7. Martian Regolith Penetration Database

7.1 Motivation

All data‑driven components require a standardised, labelled dataset of Martian regolith mechanical properties. No such comprehensive resource currently exists, though a 2025 comprehensive review has collected dispersed data from seven landing spacecraft.

7.2 Scope and Sources

We will compile, standardise, and curate data from:

· InSight HP³: penetration resistance (0.3–0.7 MPa duricrust, 4.9 \pm 0.4 MPa deeper layer), estimated cohesion (2–15 kPa), thermal profiles;
· Viking Landers: surface sampler trenching forces;
· Pathfinder Sojourner: wheel‑soil interaction;
· MER Spirit/Opportunity: wheel slip, sinkage, trenching;
· Phoenix Lander: TECP measurements;
· Curiosity (MSL) : drill feed resistance, wheel data;
· Perseverance: coring and wheel data;
· Zhurong Rover: duricrust observations at Utopia Planitia with UPRS‑1 simulant parameters.

Each entry will be labelled with: location coordinates, depth range, measurement method, estimated c, \phi, penetration resistance, bulk density, and corresponding orbital remote‑sensing signatures (thermal inertia, albedo, HiRISE texture features, reduced thermal‑inertia/albedo vectors, GLCM roughness descriptors, polygon scale, depth‑binned resistance profiles).

7.3 Use Cases

· Use‑case 1: Cross‑validation of Tier 1 MMVT (leave‑site‑out, see‑site‑in).
· Use‑case 2: Calibration of Tier 2 DGP vs. terrestrial analogs (JSC‑1, UPRS‑1, Mojave Mars Simulant).
· Use‑case 3: Benchmarking Tier 3 GNN vs. published DEM datasets (LIGGGHTS/YADE, FDM‑DEM coupled simulations).

7.4 Stress‑Case Validation Mission

"Zhurong–Elysium Utopia‑type duricrust vs. InSight–Elysium deep, unconsolidated soil" as a pair of contrasting environments where Tier 1–3 should behave differently, testing robustness of hazard classification.

7.5 Differentiation

While lunar and asteroid regolith databases exist, no Mars‑specific resource with penetration resistance data exists. This database fills a critical gap and will be released as an open‑access community resource (Zenodo).

