8. End‑to‑End Integration and Uncertainty Propagation

The three tiers are integrated into a coherent Bayesian framework that propagates uncertainty from orbit to subsurface.

Step 1 – Prior from Orbit:
Tier 1 MMVT produces p(\boldsymbol{\theta} | \mathbf{x}_{\text{orbit}}) with \boldsymbol{\theta} = [c, \phi, K, n]. For computational tractability, we approximate this as a multivariate Gaussian with mean \boldsymbol{\mu}_{\text{orbit}} and covariance \boldsymbol{\Sigma}_{\text{orbit}} derived from MC Dropout samples.

Step 2 – Posterior Update from Rover Telemetry:
Given telemetry \mathbf{D}_{\text{rover}}, Tier 2 DGP computes the posterior:

p(\boldsymbol{\theta} | \mathbf{x}_{\text{orbit}}, \mathbf{D}_{\text{rover}}) \propto p(\mathbf{D}_{\text{rover}} | \boldsymbol{\theta}) \cdot p(\boldsymbol{\theta} | \mathbf{x}_{\text{orbit}})

For efficiency, we use the orbit‑derived prior as the initial variational distribution for SVGP, then refine via ELBO maximisation.

Step 3 – Risk‑Sensitive Penetration Control:
Tier 3 GNS surrogate samples \boldsymbol{\theta}^{(m)} \sim p(\boldsymbol{\theta} | \mathbf{x}_{\text{orbit}}, \mathbf{D}_{\text{rover}}) for m = 1,\dots,M. The RL policy evaluates each sample to compute:

· Expected penetration depth \mathbb{E}[\text{depth}] = \frac{1}{M} \sum_m \text{depth}(\boldsymbol{\theta}^{(m)});
· Variance \text{Var}[\text{depth}] = \frac{1}{M} \sum_m (\text{depth}^{(m)} - \mathbb{E}[\text{depth}])^2;
· Risk‑adjusted reward r_t^{\text{risk}} = r_t - \eta \cdot \sqrt{\text{Var}[\text{depth}]}.

Step 4 – Failure Probability Quantification:
Post‑simulation, compute:

P(\text{failure}) = \mathbb{E}_{\boldsymbol{\theta}}[\mathbb{1}_{\text{depth} < 2\text{m}}] \approx \frac{1}{M} \sum_{m=1}^M \mathbb{1}_{\text{depth}^{(m)} < 2\text{m}}

along with VaR and CVaR for risk reporting.

