Appendix C: Algorithmic Details

C.1 MMVT Training Algorithm

```
Algorithm C.1: MMVT Training with MC Dropout
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Input: Dataset D = {(x_i, y_i)} (real + synthetic)
       Hyperparameters: T (MC samples), p_drop, λ_phys, epochs
Output: Trained MMVT model with uncertainty quantification

1: Initialize ViT, S3FE, MLP encoders, CrossAttention, BayesianHead
2: for epoch = 1 to epochs do
3:     for batch in Dataloader do
4:         // Forward pass through encoders
5:         Z_vision ← ViT(batch.HiRISE)
6:         Z_spec ← S3FE(batch.CRISM)
7:         Z_therm ← MLP(batch.Thermal)
8:         Z_fused ← CrossAttention(Z_vision, Z_spec, Z_therm)
9:         
10:        // MC Dropout forward passes
11:        μ_pred, σ_pred ← 0, 0
12:        for t = 1 to T do
13:            y_t ← BayesianHead(Z_fused, dropout=True)
14:            μ_pred += y_t / T
15:            σ_pred += y_t² / T
16:        end for
17:        σ_pred ← σ_pred - μ_pred²
18:        
19:        // Compute loss
20:        L_NLL ← -log N(y_true | μ_pred, σ_pred)
21:        L_KL ← KL(q(w) || p(w))
22:        L_phys ← max(0, -c_pred) + max(0, φ_pred - 50°)
23:        L_total ← L_NLL + L_KL + λ_phys * L_phys
24:        
25:        // Backward pass
26:        L_total.backward()
27:        optimizer.step()
28:     end for
29: end for
30: return model
```

C.2 SVGP Inference Algorithm

```
Algorithm C.2: Sparse Variational GP Inference
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Input: Telemetry D = {(x_i, y_i)}, inducing points Z, kernel k
Output: Posterior p(θ | D) with variational parameters m, S

1: Initialize variational parameters m (mean), S (covariance)
2: Initialize kernel hyperparameters θ_k, noise σ²
3: while not converged do
4:     // Compute Nyström approximation
5:     K_MM ← k(Z, Z)
6:     K_MN ← k(Z, X)
7:     K_NM ← K_MN^T
8:     
9:     // Compute variational expectation
10:    for i = 1 to N do
11:        μ_i ← K_NM[i,:] @ K_MM^{-1} @ m
12:        σ²_i ← k(x_i, x_i) - K_NM[i,:] @ K_MM^{-1} @ K_MN[:,i]
13:               + K_NM[i,:] @ K_MM^{-1} @ S @ K_MM^{-1} @ K_MN[:,i]
14:    end for
15:    
16:    // Compute ELBO
17:    L_ell ← Σ_i log N(y_i | μ_i, σ²_i + σ²)
18:    L_kl ← KL(N(m, S) || N(0, K_MM))
19:    L_ELBO ← L_ell - L_kl
20:    
21:    // Update parameters via gradient ascent
22:    m, S, θ_k, σ² ← Adam(L_ELBO)
23: end while
24: return m, S, θ_k, σ²
```

C.3 DYNAMI-CAL GRAPHNET Forward Pass

```
Algorithm C.3: Momentum-Conserving GNS Forward Pass
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Input: Graph G = (V, E) with node features v_i, edge features e_ij
       Number of message passing steps K
Output: Predicted node accelerations â_i

1: // Encoder
2: for each node i do
3:     h_i⁰ ← MLP_enc(v_i)
4: end for
5: for each edge (i,j) do
6:     h_ij⁰ ← MLP_edge(e_ij)
7: end for
8:
9: // Message passing with momentum conservation
10: for k = 0 to K-1 do
11:     for each edge (i,j) do
12:         m_ij^k ← MLP_msg(h_i^k, h_j^k, h_ij^k)
13:         // Enforce Newton's Third Law: F_ij = -F_ji
14:         m_ij^k ← (m_ij^k - m_ji^k) / 2
15:     end for
16:     
17:     // Aggregate messages
18:     for each node i do
19:         M_i^k ← Σ_{j∈N(i)} m_ij^k
20:     end for
21:     
22:     // Update node states
23:     for each node i do
24:         h_i^{k+1} ← MLP_node(h_i^k, M_i^k)
25:     end for
26:     
27:     // Project to satisfy momentum conservation
28:     Δa ← compute_acceleration_update(h^{k+1})
29:     Δa ← project_momentum_constraints(Δa, masses, positions)
30: end for
31:
32: // Decoder
33: for each node i do
34:     â_i ← MLP_dec(h_i^K)
35: end for
36:
37: return {â_i}
```

C.4 PPO Training with Domain Randomization

```
Algorithm C.4: PPO Training with Domain Randomization
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Input: GNS surrogate environment, hyperparameters
Output: Trained policy π_θ, value function V_φ

1: Initialize policy π_θ, value function V_φ
2: Initialize environment encoder GRU_ψ
3: for iteration = 1 to N_iterations do
4:     // Sample domain randomization parameters
5:     c ∼ U(0, 25), φ ∼ U(20°, 45°), h ∼ U(5, 50)
6:     reset environment with (c, φ, h)
7:     
8:     // Collect trajectories
9:     D ← []
10:    for t = 1 to T do
